sections.content:
If you forget to update the loop variable, you'll create an **infinite loop** — your program will run forever (or until your browser crashes). Always ask yourself: **"What changes each time so that the loop will eventually stop?"**

```javascript
// 🚨 DANGER: Infinite loop!
let x = 1;
while (x <= 10) {
  console.log(x);
  // Oops! We forgot x = x + 1;
  // x is ALWAYS 1, so x <= 10 is ALWAYS true
}
```

