sections.content:
```javascript
function add(a, b) {
  console.log(a + b);
}

add(5, 3);    // 8 — works fine
add(5);       // NaN — b is undefined, 5 + undefined = NaN
add();        // NaN — both are undefined
add(1, 2, 3); // 3 — extra argument (3) is silently ignored
```

JavaScript doesn't throw an error for mismatched arguments — it just uses `undefined` for missing ones. This can lead to subtle bugs, so always be careful to pass the right number of arguments.

