sections.content:
A NodeList from `querySelectorAll` supports `.forEach()` but not `.map()`, `.filter()`, or `.reduce()`. To get full array powers:

```javascript
const links = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-link');

// Method 1: Array.from()
const linksArray = Array.from(links);

// Method 2: Spread operator
const linksArray2 = [...links];

// Now you can use .map(), .filter(), etc.!
const linkTexts = linksArray.map(link => link.textContent);
console.log(linkTexts); // ["Home", "About", "Contact"]
```

