sections.content:
A common gotcha: `element.style` can only read styles set directly via JavaScript or the HTML `style` attribute. It does NOT see styles from CSS files or `<style>` tags.

```javascript
// CSS file says: h1 { color: blue; }
const h1 = document.querySelector('h1');
console.log(h1.style.color); // "" — Empty! Even though h1 IS blue!

// To read the ACTUAL computed style, use getComputedStyle:
const computed = getComputedStyle(h1);
console.log(computed.color); // "rgb(0, 0, 255)" — The actual blue!
```

