sections.content:
HTML **attributes** and DOM **properties** are related but NOT always the same:

```javascript
const input = document.querySelector('input');

// HTML: <input type="text" value="initial">
// User types "hello" in the input

// ATTRIBUTE reflects the HTML source (original value)
console.log(input.getAttribute('value')); // "initial"

// PROPERTY reflects the current state
console.log(input.value); // "hello" (what the user typed)
```

**Rule of thumb:**
- Use **properties** (dot notation) for standard attributes: `el.id`, `el.href`, `el.src`, `el.className`, `el.value`
- Use **getAttribute/setAttribute** for custom attributes or when you specifically need the HTML attribute value
- Use **dataset** for data-* attributes (next section!)

