```javascript
// ❌ WRONG — Don't do this
button.addEventListener('click', function() { ... });

// ✅ RIGHT — Listen on the form
form.addEventListener('submit', function(event) {
  event.preventDefault();
  // ...
});
```
Listening on the submit button's `click` event misses when users press **Enter** to submit the form. The `submit` event on the form catches BOTH cases. Always listen for `submit` on the `<form>` element.

